what are the types of verbs?
There are several types of verbs, including: 
1. Action Verbs - These describe physical actions or movements (e.g., run, jump). 
2. Linking Verbs - These connect two sentences and do not express action on their own (e.g., appears, seems). 
3. Helping Verbs - These assist the main verb in forming tenses or voice (e.g., am, has been). 
4. Auxiliary Verbs - These are helping verbs that can be used with other auxiliaries to form complex tenses (e.g., do, have).
